<i>noun</i>: 순진 [순진], 순수 [순수], 무죄 [무죄/무줴], 무구 [무구], 결백 [결백] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>순진 [순진]</dt><br>
<dd>1. innocence</dd><br>
<dd>마음이 꾸밈이 없고 참됨.</dd><br>
<dd>The quality of being genuine.</dd><br>
<dd>2. naivety</dd><br>
<dd>세상 물정을 잘 몰라 어수룩함.</dd><br>
<dd>The quality of being naïve because of lack of experience of life or worldliness.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>순수 [순수]</dt><br>
<dd>1. purity</dd><br>
<dd>다른 것이 전혀 섞이지 않음.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of not being mixed with other things.</dd><br>
<dd>2. purity; innocence; guilelessness</dd><br>
<dd>개인적인 욕심이나 못된 생각이 없음.</dd><br>
<dd>A lack of personal desire or evil thoughts.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>무죄 [무죄/무줴]</dt><br>
<dd>1. innocence</dd><br>
<dd>아무런 잘못이나 죄가 없음.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of having not done anything wrong or committed a crime.</dd><br>
<dd>2. innocence</dd><br>
<dd>법률상 죄가 되지 않는 것으로 밝혀짐. 또는 그런 상태에 있음.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of someone being found not guilty by law, or being in such a state.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>무구 [무구]</dt><br>
<dd>1. innocence; purity</dd><br>
<dd>때가 묻지 않고 맑고 깨끗함.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of being clean and pure without being stained.</dd><br>
<dd>2. innocence; purity</dd><br>
<dd>꾸밈없이 본래 그대로 순박함.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of being innocent without artificiality.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>결백 [결백]</dt><br>
<dd>innocence</dd><br>
<dd>잘못이나 죄를 저지른 것이 없음.</dd><br>
<dd>Not having committed a wrongdoing or sin.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>